'''Mohammad Abu Al-Nadi''' ({{langx|ar|محمد ابو النادي}}; born 8 February 2001) is a professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Malaysia Super League]] side [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportingkc.com/players/mo-abualnadi/|title=Mo Abualnadi|first=Sporting Kansas|last=City|website=Sporting Kansas City}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportingkc.com/news/swope-park-rangers-sign-sporting-kc-academy-trio-mo-abualnadi-jake-davis-and-sea|title=Swope Park Rangers sign Sporting KC Academy trio Mo Abualnadi, Jake Davis and Sean Karani to Academy contracts|first=Sporting Kansas|last=City|website=Sporting Kansas City}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://und.com/roster/mohammad-abualnadi/|title=Mohammad Abualnadi|date=July 15, 2019|website=Notre Dame Fighting Irish - Official Athletics Website}}</ref> Born in the United States, he plays for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Early life==
Abu Al-Nadi was born in [[Overland Park, Kansas|Overland Park]], [[Kansas]], United States, where he attended [[Blue Valley High School]].<ref name="auto1">{{cite web |title=Mohammad Abualnadi - Bio |url=https://pittsburghpanthers.com/sports/mens-soccer/roster/mohammad-abualnadi/12126 |website=pittsburghpanthers.com |publisher=Pittsburgh Panthers |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref> He played futsal in his youth.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Scavuzzo |first1=Diane |title=U.S. YOUTH FUTSAL 2015 NATIONAL TEAMS ANNOUNCED |url=https://www.soccertoday.com/u-s-youth-futsal-2015-national-teams-announced/?cn-reloaded=1 |website=soccertoday.com |publisher=SoccerToday |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=23 July 2015}}</ref> He played for a year round club, European Soccer Institute (ESI), for two years before joining [[Sporting Kansas City]]'s academy for two years while at high school. He helped lead Sporting KC's U19 squad to the fourth seed in the playoffs and made the quarterfinals of the USSDA tournament.<ref name="auto1"/>

==University career==
Abu Al-Nadi played two years of [[College soccer in the United States|college soccer]] for the [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish men's soccer|Notre Dame Fighting Irish]], as well as one year at [[Pittsburgh Panthers men's soccer|Pittsburgh Panthers]].

During his [[freshman]] year in 2019, Abu Al-Nadi played in all 19 matches, earning 15 starts as a defender during his rookie season. He earned his first start in his Notre Dame debut in the season-opening win at [[Saint Louis Billikens men's soccer|Saint Louis]]. He finished the season with a goal and an assist. He scored the first goal of his career at the 1:12 mark of the season opener, which was tied for the second fastest goal to open a match since the 1995 season. He provided an assist for the game-winning goal in the 1-0 victory over [[Duke Blue Devils men's soccer|Duke]].<ref name="auto3">{{cite web |title=Mohammad Abualnadi - Bio |url=https://fightingirish.com/roster/mohammad-abualnadi/ |website=fightingirish.com |date=15 July 2019 |publisher=Notre Dame Fighting Irish |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref>

As a [[sophomore]] in 2020, he played in 16 matches, earning 15 starts as a defender during his sophomore campaign. He also earned starts in five of Notre Dame’s clean sheet wins.<ref name="auto3"/>

On 9 August 2021, Abu Al-Nadi [[NCAA transfer portal|transferred]] to the [[Pittsburgh Panthers men's soccer|Pittsburgh Panthers]] as a [[Junior (education year)|junior]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pitt men's soccer signs eight newcomers, including five freshmen |url=https://www.soccerwire.com/news/pitt-mens-soccer-signs-eight-newcomers-including-five-freshmen/ |website=soccerwire.com |publisher=Soccer Wire |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=9 August 2021}}</ref> He appeared in 15 games, starting in 14 of them. He was also named to the All-ACC Academic Team for the first time in his career, posting a 3.48 fall GPA.<ref name="auto1"/>

The following year, Abu Al-Nadi registered a goal and an assist in a draw against [[Akron Zips men's soccer|Akron]].<ref>{{cite web |title=No. 10 Panthers Earn Draw With No. 14 Akron |url=https://pittsburghpanthers.com/news/2022/9/19/mens-soccer-no-10-panthers-earn-draw-with-no-14-akron.aspx |website=pittsburghpanthers.com |publisher=Pittsburgh Panthers |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=19 September 2022}}</ref> He started in seven of nine games that year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohammad Abualnadi - Statistics |url=https://pittsburghpanthers.com/sports/mens-soccer/roster/mohammad-abualnadi/12126 |website=pittsburghpanthers.com |publisher=Pittsburgh Panthers |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Swope Park Rangers/Sporting Kansas City II===
On 8 March 2019, Abu Al-Nadi signed with [[Swope Park Rangers]] as an amateur player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Swope Park Rangers sign Sporting KC Academy trio Mo Abualnadi, Jake Davis and Sean Karani to Academy contracts |url=https://www.sportingkc.com/news/swope-park-rangers-sign-sporting-kc-academy-trio-mo-abualnadi-jake-davis-and-sea |website=sportingkc.com |publisher=Sporting KC |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=8 March 2019}}</ref> He made his club debut against [[Pittsburgh Riverhounds]] in a 2-2 draw.<ref name="auto2">{{cite web |title=Sporting KC II signs 21-year-old defender and Academy product Mo Abualnadi |url=https://www.sportingkc.com/skcii/news/sporting-kc-ii-signs-21-year-old-defender-and-academy-product-mo-abualnadi |website=sportingkc.com |publisher=Sporting KC |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref>

On 30 January 2023, Abu Al-Nadi signed with [[Sporting Kansas City II]] to an [[MLS Next Pro]] professional contract.<ref name="auto2"/> On 13 July 2023, Sporting Kansas City II mutually agrees to part ways with defender Abu Al-Nadi.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sporting Kansas City II mutually agrees to part ways with defender Mo Abualnadi |url=https://www.oursportscentral.com/services/releases/sporting-kc-ii-mutually-agrees-to-part-ways-with-defender-mo-abualnadi/n-5988792 |website=oursportscentral.com |publisher=OurSportsCentral |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=13 July 2023}}</ref>

===Sporting Kansas City===
On 26 April 2023, Abu Al-Nadi made his first-team debut for [[Sporting Kansas City]], appearing in a [[2023 U.S. Open Cup|Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup]] matchup against [[Tulsa Athletic]], resulting in a 3-0 victory. Abu Al-Nadi's first-team debut began in the 81st minute when he came on for [[Robert Voloder]] at left-back. The defender won two of three duels and made two tackles in just under 10 minutes of play.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Belzer |first1=Jared |title=Trio of SKC II players make first-team debuts in US Open Cup win |url=https://www.sportingkc.com/news/trio-of-skc-ii-players-make-first-team-debuts-in-us-open-cup-win |website=sportingkc.com |publisher=Sporting KC |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=26 April 2023}}</ref>

===Al-Hussein (Irbid)===
On 13 July 2023, Mohammad Abu Al-Nadi signed a two-year contract with [[Jordanian Pro League]] club [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يتعاقد مع أبو النادي |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1254255 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=13 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=ابرز ما شهده الميركاتو الأردني في ساعاته الأخيرة |url=https://www.khaberni.com/news/%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B2-%D9%85%D8%A7-%D8%B4%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-601362 |website=khaberni.com |publisher=Khaberni |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=17 July 2023}}</ref>

===Al-Qasim===
On 22 August 2024, Abu Al-Nadi signed a contract with [[Iraq Stars League]] club [[Al-Qasim SC|Al-Qasim]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Almaalouma |title=الأردني أبو النادي آخر المحترفين الملتحقين بفريق القاسم |url=https://almaalomah.me/news/74091/sports/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D8%A8%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%82%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%85 |website=almaalomah.me |publisher=Al-Maalomah |language=Arabic |date=22 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=أبو النادي يحترف في العراق |url=https://www.addustour.com/articles/1437204-%D8%A3%D8%A8%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%81-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82 |website=addustor.com |publisher=Ad-Dustor |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=23 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= السوري أيمن الحكيم يوقع عقدًا جديدًا مع القاسم العراقي |url= https://www.winwin.com/كرة-قدم/الأخبار/السوري-أيمن-الحكيم-يوقع-عقدًا-جديدًا-مع-القاسم-العراقي |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=25 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=4 September 2024}}</ref>

A month after his move, Abu Al-Nadi had already expressed his desire to terminate his contract with the club through a contractual clause, after Malaysian side [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]] offered him a deal to join their club.<ref>{{cite web |title= السوري أيمن الحكيم يوقع عقدًا جديدًا مع القاسم العراقي |url= https://www.winwin.com/كرة-قدم/الأخبار/مدافع-الأردن-محمد-أبو-النادي-يسعى-للرحيل-عن-الدوري-العراقي |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=25 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=14 September 2024}}</ref>

===Selangor FC===
On 24 September 2024, Abu Al-Nadi joined [[Malaysia Super League]] side [[Selangor F.C.|Selangor]], just before the transfer deadline.<ref>{{cite web |title= Mohammad Abualnadi #IsRed |url= https://selangorfc.com/en/news/3489/Mohammad%20Abualnadi%20IsRed |website=selangorfc.com |publisher=Selangor F.C. |access-date=25 September 2024 |language=English |date=25 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= رسميا.. أبو النادي ينضم إلى الدوري الماليزي |url= https://m.kooora.com/?n=1357106&pg=1&o=n |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=25 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=25 September 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Abu Al-Nadi began his international career in 2019 by appearing for the [[Jordan national under-19 football team]] in a set of friendlies against Qatar's [[Aspire Academy]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web |last1=Belzer |first1=Jared |title=Sporting KC II defender Mo Abualnadi called in for Jordan Olympic National Team training camp |url=https://www.sportingkcacademy.com/news_article/show/1265142 |website=sportingkcacademy.com |publisher=Sporting KC Academy |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=17 March 2023}}</ref>

On 17 March 2023, Abu Al-Nadi was called in for a [[Jordan national under-23 football team|Jordan Olympic national team]] training camp in Lebanon from March 19–29.<ref name="auto"/> On 8 June 2023, Abu Al-Nadi was called up to the [[Jordan national under-23 football team|Jordan U-23]] squad for the [[2023 WAFF U-23 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Belzer |first1=Jared |title=Sporting KC II defender Mo Abualnadi called up to Jordan U-23 West Asia Championship roster |url=https://www.sportingkc.com/skcii/news/sporting-kc-ii-defender-mo-abualnadi-called-up-to-jordan-u-23-west-asia-champion |website=sportingkc.com |publisher=Sporting KC |access-date=1 September 2024 |date=9 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الوطني ت23 ينهي تحضيراته لـ "غرب آسيا" ويغادر إلى العراق غداً |url=https://twitter.com/JordanFA/status/1666840922364030984 |website=Twitter.com |publisher=Jordan FA |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |format=Tweet |date=8 June 2023}}</ref> On 26 August 2023, Abu Al-Nadi was called up once again to take part in the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification]] process.<ref>{{cite web |title=إعلان القائمة الأولية للمنتخب الوطني تحت 23 عاما للتصفيات الآسيوية |url=https://www.almamlakatv.com/news/123875-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-23-%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=almamlakattv.com |publisher=Al-Mamlaka |language=Arabic |date=26 August 2023}}</ref> He went on to appear for Jordan at the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jfa.jo/news.php?id=29736&title=%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AA23-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9|title=إعلان القائمة الأولية للمنتخب الوطني ت23 لمعسكر قطر والنهائيات الآسيوية|trans-title=Announcing the preliminary list of the U23 national team for the Qatar camp and the Asian Cup finals|publisher=Jordan Football Association|date=6 April 2024}}</ref>

On 7 July, Mohammad Abu Al-Nadi received a call-up to the [[Jordan national football team]], participating in a training camp consisting of local players on July 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=فرق المقدمة بـ"المحترفين" تسيطر على قائمة "النشامى" المحلية |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%80-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-1755115 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=7 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=السلامي يعلن قائمة منتخب الأردن لمعسكر تركيا |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1339446 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=7 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=منتخب النشامى يهزم إسبارطة التركي ويلتقي نيفتشي غدًا |url=https://www.addustour.com/articles/1430675-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%8A%D9%87%D8%B2%D9%85-%D8%A5%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%8A-%D8%BA%D8%AF%D9%8B%D8%A7 |website=addustor.com |publisher=Ad-Dustor |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=21 July 2024}}</ref> On 23 August 2024, Mohammad Abu Al-Nadi received another international call-up to the senior team, as a part of preparations for World Cup qualification [[North Korea]].<ref>{{cite web |title=إعلان قائمة النشامى لمواجهتي الكويت وفلسطين بتصفيات كأس العالم (أسماء) |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/869561 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=23 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=النشامى يباشر تحضيراته للدور الحاسم ضمن تصفيات كأس العالم |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/869788 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=23 August 2024}}</ref> He made his debut for the national team on 27 August 2024 against North Korea.<ref>{{cite web |title=تفاصيل مباراة الأردن و كوريا الشمالية |url=https://jfa.com.jo/arsh_match.php?id_mon=1&id1=1102 |website=jfa.jo |publisher=Jordan Football Association |access-date=6 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=27 August 2024}}</ref>

On 30 August 2024, Abu Al-Nadi received his first proper senior international call-up, to take part in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] process.<ref>{{cite web |title=القائمة النهائية للنشامى في مواجهتي الكويت وفلسطين.. أسماء |url=https://factjo.com/news.aspx?Id=215597 |website=factjo.com |publisher=Al-Haqiqa International |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=30 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=سلامي يعلن قائمة "النشامى" لمباراتي الكويت وفلسطين ويحدد أولوياته |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D9%88%D9%81%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B7%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%AF%D8%AF-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87-1801268 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |access-date=1 September 2024 |language=Arabic |date=30 August 2024}}</ref>

